# Let's get started

Here is some text I've added.

Now have some code as well:

```{r setup, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE}
library(tidyverse)


#Let's read in some data
mn = read_csv(file = "mn-schools.csv")
mn
```
```{r plot, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, fig.width=6, fig.height=6, out.width="50%", fig.align='center', fig.cap="**Figure 1.** *A scatterplot of graduation rates vs SAT scores.*"}
#scatter plot of graduation rates vs SAT scores
ggplot(data = mn, aes(x = grad, y = sat)) + 
  theme_light() +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue", size = 4) +
  labs(x = "Graduation Rate", y = "Average SAT Score")
```
Google "knitr" to see more fig. options!

The mean graduation rate is `r round(mean(mn$grad), 2)`.


